Two men died in the early hours of Tuesday morning after being struck by a moving train in Tongaat. Police spokesperson, Colonel Thembeka Mbele said that the two men, who are believed to be in their twenties, were allegedly asleep on the railway line at the Tongaat Train Station when they were struck. “Circumstances surrounding the incident are being investigated. An inquest docket is being investigated by Tongaat SAPS,” said Mbele. Local emergency service, Reaction Unit SA (RUSA), also responded to the incident and said that the men were allegedly decapitated by a goods train. Rusa spokesperson, Prem Balram said; “A passer-by contacted (RUSA) at approximately 6 20 am and reported the incident. “It is alleged that the two men were vagrants who slept under a bridge next to the railway line. Circumstances leading up to the incident has not been established at this stage.”